The Federal Government is to establish at least one Police forensics laboratory in each of the six geo-political zones in the country. The move is to enhance police investigation capacity, the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF) Mr Boss Gida Mustapha has said. He was speaking yesterday in Abuja at a roundtable to validate the Bureau of Public Service Reforms (BPSR) study on “Mapping the Process of Obtaining Bail at the Nigeria Police Station” aimed at improving the police bail process. Represented by the Permanent Secretary, General Services Office (GSO) in the Office of the OSGF Olusegun Adekunle, Mustapha also said government has put in place short-term measures to combat kidnapping across the country. The Acting Director General of the BPSR, Mr Dasuki Arabi said the study was carried out in three phases.